It can get very crowded during lunch time so be prepared to have to wait if you come during that time. The staff works as hard as possible it seems and tries to be friendly for the most part. If you come during non-rush times they are much friendlier. It's subway so lots of subway choices to choose from with different bread choices including different toppings as in all subway restaurants around the world. The price is inexpensive and can be a healthy alternative for a lunch. Get the subway rewards card and go there often it builds up quickly (unlike other rewards programs) I've had over a dozen free sandwiches.
